  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And they made a proclamation through Judah and Jerusalem,.... By heralds appointed for the purpose: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "to bring in to the Lord; into the house of the Lord, and for the reparation of it; and so for his service, honour, and glory: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "the collection that Moses the servant of the Lord laid upon Israel in the wilderness; not to bring in the tabernacle of Moses, as the Targum here and in 2 Chronicles 24:6, but such a voluntary gift as Moses moved the children of Israel to bring, when in the wilderness, for the service of the tabernacle. ",
        "children": [
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "the collection that Moses the servant of the Lord laid upon Israel in the wilderness; not to bring in the tabernacle of Moses, as the Targum here and in ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "2 Chronicles 24:6",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": ", but such a voluntary gift as Moses moved the children of Israel to bring, when in the wilderness, for the service of the tabernacle. ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
